    "summary": "Currently working as Chief Accounting Officer at Philips and in this role I am a close partner to the CFO and member of the Philips Finance Leadership Team. I have global responsibility for Philips\u2019 Technical Accounting, Internal Control (SOx), and Corporate Reporting (SEC and AFM) function and have responsibility to oversight on accounting and ensuring IFRS and local statutory compliance. \n\nWorked 5 years as Chief Accountant at Signify (formerly known as Philips Lighting) and responsible for Technical Accounting, External Reporting and Internal Control. Overseeing the organization\u2019s accounting and internal control function including ensuring compliance with accounting standards and practices. Managing and delivering external financial statements and ensuring integrity of all financial information.\n\nWorked before as director financial reporting & control at OCI NV, a Dutch listed company in the Fertilizer and Chemicals industry. Responsible for the external and internal reporting (including FP&A) for group purposes. \n\nPreviously I was a Senior Director at PwC focussed on transactions and accounting and reporting matters. One of the experienced leaders in PwC's Capital Markets and Accounting Advisory Services group in Amsterdam.\n\nPeople  highly value my drive, clarity and focus that I bring to inherent uncertainties around transactions, as well as my practical experience and pragmatism.\n\nI have extensive experience in transactions and deep technical accounting skills (IFRS, NL GAAP, US GAAP). I supported many clients during various small and large transaction processes by providing advice and support on accounting  structuring, vendor assistance, purchase price accounting, carve outs, gaap conversions, accounting policy and reporting alignment. \n\nWithin PwC I have had internal roles in the area of Risk & Quality, Operations and coaching an enthusiastic group of inspiring professionals.\n\nIn years 2012 and 2013 I was part time seconded to a client and worked as interim group controller of an AEX company in the Netherlands, reporting to the CFO and audit committee. In this role I was responsible for internal and external reporting, handling the carve out and sale of one of their divisions, interacting with accountants, advisors and the AFM.",
